'''Yatsuakata Sukune no Kami''' (八縣宿禰神) is an ancient Japanese figure or {{ill|kami|ja|神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

== Overview ==
Yatsuakata Sukune no Kami is also referred to as '''八県宿禰神''', '''箭津安賀多神''' (Yatsuakata no Kami), '''八縣宿祢命''', or '''佐和惠多良六老彦神''' (Saweetara - exact reading unknown - Hiko no Kami). At the {{ill|Shinkai Sansha Shrine|ja|新海三社神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Yatsuakata is considered either the child of {{ill|Takeminakata no Kami|ja|建御名方神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} or a name for {{ill|Okata no Kami|ja|大縣神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The offspring, {{ill|Takeshina no Mikoto|ja|健志奈乃命|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, is described in the ''Suho Suwa Clan Genealogy'' as distinct from {{ill|Takeshina no Mikoto|ja|蓼科神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a child of Takeminakata. He is recognized as the progenitor deity of the {{ill|Suwa clan|ja|諏訪氏|1=Suwa clan|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

The deity first appears in the historical record in the {{ill|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|ja|日本三代実録|qq=draft|qq=draft}} as holding the Rank of {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank|ja|従五位|1=Junior Fifth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Lower. On the 9th day of the 3rd month of {{ill|Jogan|ja|貞観|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 10 (868 CE), Yatsuakata was elevated to the Rank of {{ill|Senior Fifth Rank|ja|正五位|1=Senior Fifth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Lower.{{Sfn|Nobukazu|1985|p=23}}

== Genealogy ==
[[File:Moriya Family Tree - 守矢氏系図.png|thumb|center|200px|Genealogy of the first five generations of the {{ill|Moriya clan|ja|守矢氏|1=Moriya clan|qq=draft|qq=draft}}]]

Yatsuakata Sukune no Kami is the child of {{ill|Izuhayao no Mikoto|ja|出早雄命|1=Izuhayao-no-Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
, who is himself the son of {{ill|Takeminakata no Kami|ja|建御名方神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Yasakatome no Kami|ja|八坂刀売神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Yatsuakata's mother may have been {{ill|Tamaru-hime|ja|多満留姫|1=Tamaru-hime|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. He had siblings, including {{ill|Kamohagami|ja|可毛羽神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Wakakihime|ja|若木比売神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kusanaihime|ja|草奈井比売神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Izuhayahime|ja|伊津早姫神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, as well as {{ill|Okata no Kami|ja|大縣神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Uchiakata no Kami|ja|内安賀多神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Sotakata no Kami|ja|外安賀多神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Some genealogies also include {{ill|Aizuhime no Kami|ja|会津比売神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, described as either a sibling or offspring of Yatsuakata.{{Sfn|Jinosuke|1912|p=73}}

== Shrines Dedicated to Yatsuakata Sukune no Kami ==
* Former {{ill|Shichisha Myojin|ja|七社明神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (now defunct, located in Tamagawa, Chino City, Nagano Prefecture)
* {{ill|Shinkai Sansha Shrine|ja|新海三社神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Taguchi Miyashiro, Saku City, Nagano Prefecture)
* {{ill|Goka Hachiman Shrine|ja|五加八幡神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Goka, Ueda City, Nagano Prefecture)
* {{ill|Kirigafuri no Miya|ja|霧降宮切久保諏訪神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Kirikubo, Hakuba Village, Nagano Prefecture)

