'''Yatsuakata Sukune no Kami''' (八縣宿禰神) is an ancient Japanese figure or {{ill|kami|ja|神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/kami|qq=}}.

== Overview ==
Yatsuakata Sukune no Kami is also referred to as '''八県宿禰神''', '''箭津安賀多神''' (Yatsuakata no Kami), '''八縣宿祢命''', or '''佐和惠多良六老彦神''' (Saweetara - exact reading unknown - Hiko no Kami). At the {{ill|Shinkai Sansha Shrine|ja|新海三社神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinkai Sansha Shrine|qq=}}, Yatsuakata is considered either the child of {{ill|Takeminakata|lt=Takeminakata|lt=Takeminakata no Kami|ja|建御名方神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeminakata no Kami|qq=}} or a name for {{ill|Okata no Kami|ja|大縣神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Okata no Kami|qq=}}. The offspring, {{ill|Takeshina no Mikoto|ja|健志奈乃命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeshina no Mikoto|qq=}}, is described in the ''Suho Suwa Clan Genealogy'' as distinct from {{ill|Takeshina no Mikoto|ja|蓼科神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeshina no Mikoto|qq=}}, a child of Takeminakata. He is recognized as the progenitor deity of the {{ill|Suwa clan|ja|諏訪氏|1=Suwa clan|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa clan|qq=}}.

The deity first appears in the historical record in the {{ill|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|ja|日本三代実録|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|qq=}} as holding the Rank of {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank|ja|従五位|1=Junior Fifth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}} Lower. On the 9th day of the 3rd month of {{ill|Jogan|ja|貞観|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jogan|qq=}} 10 (868 CE), Yatsuakata was elevated to the Rank of {{ill|Senior Fifth Rank|ja|正五位|1=Senior Fifth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Fifth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Fifth Rank|qq=}} Lower.{{Sfn|Nobukazu|1985|p=23}}

== Genealogy ==
