'''Yatsuakata Sukune no Kami''' (八縣宿禰神) is an ancient Japanese figure or [[:en:Deity|kami]].
== Overview == Yatsuakata Sukune no Kami is also referred to as '''八県宿禰神''', '''箭津安賀多神''' (Yatsuakata no Kami), '''八縣宿祢命''', or '''佐和惠多良六老彦神''' (Saweetara - exact reading unknown - Hiko no Kami). At the {{ill|Shinkai Sansha Shrine|ja|新海三社神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinkai Sansha Shrine|qq=}}, Yatsuakata is considered either the child of {{ill|Takeminakata|lt=Takeminakata|lt=Takeminakata no Kami|ja|建御名方神|1=Takeminakata|2=ja|3=タケミナカタ|lt=Takeminakata|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeminakata no Kami|qq=}} or a name for {{ill|Okata no Kami|ja|大縣神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Okata no Kami|qq=}}. The offspring, {{ill|Takeshina no Mikoto|ja|健志奈乃命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeshina no Mikoto|qq=}}, is described in the ''Suho Suwa Clan Genealogy'' as distinct from {{ill|Takeshina no Mikoto|ja|蓼科神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeshina no Mikoto|qq=}}, a child of Takeminakata. He is recognized as the progenitor deity of the [[:en:Suwa clan|Suwa clan]].
